---
description: Data, replay and determinism rules
alwaysApply: true
---

All historical, feature, research and decision workflows must be deterministic and point-in-time safe.

Requirements:

- No direct wall-clock calls in replayable code.
- Use injected clocks.
- No unseeded randomness.
- No live database reads during replay.
- Pin datasets and configuration.
- Preserve canonical event ordering.
- Use event time, effective time and known-at time correctly.
- Support effective-date-aware symbol resolution.
- Support corporate actions.
- Handle duplicates explicitly.
- Handle late data explicitly.
- Handle stale data explicitly.
- Do not compare floating-point values for financial equality.
- Use canonical serialization before hashing.
- Same input, configuration and code version must produce the same output.
- Offline and online feature definitions must remain compatible.
- Research, backtest, paper and live must share core contracts where practical.
